Impact of Long-Term Care on Retirement Wellness.

Rappaport AM.

Retirement wellness is the result of retiring at an appropriate age, saving 
enough and managing risks appropriately. One of the major risks that often is 
not addressed effectively is the long-term care (LTC) risk, i.e., the risk of 
needing help due to physical or cognitive limitations. In 2014, the Society of 
Actuaries issued a call for papers on the link between LTC and retirement 
security. This article will discuss the topic of LTC and retirement security 
broadly, drawing from several of the papers. Some of the topics include the 
impact of LTC on the individual, family members and caregivers; modeling results 
showing the impact of LTC on assets needed for a secure retirement; alternative 
methods of financing LTC; the link between housing decisions and LTC; and some 
ideas for the future.

