PMID: 26514019 [Indexed for MEDLINE]


217. Seishin Shinkeigaku Zasshi. 2015;117(2):132-45.

[What Lessons Should We Learn from the Death of Patients on Xeplion?].

[Article in Japanese]

Fujii Y.

From the launch of the long-acting injectable antipsychotic paliperidone 
palmitate (XEPLION) on November 19, 2013, 32 fatal cases had been reported up to 
May 18, 2014 (estimated number of users is approximately 11,000 patients) in the 
Early Post-marketing Phase Vigilance. The most common cause of death was sudden 
death (12 cases were sudden death defined by ICD-10 codes 96.0 and 96.1 and 4 
cases suspected sudden death), followed by suicide (7 cases), and neuroleptic 
malignant syndrome (4 cases). Several deaths occurred involving patients with 
